A low rate of trisomy 21 in twin-pregnancies: a cytogenetics retrospective study of 278 cases. From January 1st 1990 until December 31st 2001, we collected 19686 prenatal diagnosis (on amniocentesis and chorius villus sampling). Five hundred twelve samples (2.6%) concerned 278 twin pregnancies. The most frequent indications were maternal age > or = 35 years (108/278 = 38.8%), medically assisted procreation (34/278 = 12.3%), positive ultrasound (20/278 = 7.2%). Chromosome abnormalities were found in eight twin-pregnancies (2.9%): five with only one fetus affected [47,XX,+ 18 45,XX,t( 13